  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purposes of this study are to compare the outcomes of the biodegradable implants for the
      fixation of ankle fracture and those of metallic implants, and to assess the problems of the
      biodegradable implants. Null hypothesis is that the clinical outcomes of biodegradable plate
      and screws for ankle fracture are not different from those of metallic implants.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
